 My point is I have heard this same thread over, and over, and over.  I have played for several years...And I do not see a real difference between the classes.<br>
  Any class played well, and equipped properly do excellent jobs in the right situation.  <br>
<br>
  &quot;A man has to know his limitations&quot;<br>
<br>
  My mid level Ranger, equipped with mid level quested armor, and played sort of well, outlasts most of the other rangers, and most other warriors, monks, pallies, and rouges that I have played with of a similiar level.  Aside from my screw-ups, I know how to manage argo, when to hit the taunt button, and how to pull, etc.  <br>
  The only class I have seen that seems not to get waxed with equal speed is Bards, they seem to be able to run faster, charm the adds, and not get argo...Oh how I wish I could sing!  I have not noticed a great overbalancing class yet, in a given situation a certian class can excel, but that same class will fail in other situations.<br>
<br>
  These are only my opinions and they reflect my experiances.  I started a ranger back in the old days before the first expansion.  I have always played rangers, I do not understand why anyone would play anything else.  But for some reason they seem to &lt;boogled&gt;<br>
<br>
  My favorite group is 5 rangers and a druid or bard.  Whoooohoo how the monsters drop.<br>
