<br>
Rogues though arent designed to be tanks. Rangers at least can claim to be a tank based on the fact they are part warrior and have a taunt ability.<br>
<br>
Can a rogue tank? Sure they can. Any melee class can tank. But the power of a rogue is in the damage done by backstabbing so tanking is a waste of the rogues abilities.<br>
<br>
It is a simple reality that if a competent plate class tank is available and the ranger isnt extremely higher than said plate tank, then the ranger shouldnt be taking agro on purpose.The ranger is not a efficient tank in that situaution compared to the plate tank. Can a ranger take agro? probably......but they shouldnt if they can avoid it.<br>
<br>
After 40 and in the new world zones, mobs hit to hard to effectively tank as a mediocrely equiped ranger, but plate class tanks can be less equiped and still tank efficiently. I have 1009 ac self buffed at 56 and it will go up a bit more when I get my 2 points of defense in that level. I Have a little 0ver 2300 hp self buffed. But I am not mediocrely equiped. I dont have the best stuff out there but I have good equipment. I purposefully have worked on raising my ac. Reality is that after 900 though, the additional ac is not that much more effective.<br>
<br>
Rangers are tanks, but they are not the preferred tank usually after 40. Anyone that claims a ranger is ALWAYS a better tank then a warrior , shadowknight or paladin, is living in a dream world. Individual Rangers may be better than certain warriors, shadowknights or paladins at different times and in different situations, but the general rule is that a plate tank is more efficient because of AC and HP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1387<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/19/02 2:49:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1402.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rangers trade ..</span><hr size=1> Actually, I prefer rangers by and large as tanks in high level exp grind groups.  However, that is a situation where the mobs are noticeably lower than the tank.  <br>
